you will visit Human Resources to fill out various employment  tax  and payroll forms  Please refer to the Employment Forms listed under the HR Forms link on the left side of the webpage for a complete list of the forms  Ensure that you bring the required identification document s  necessary to complete the I 9 Employment Verification Eligibility form  The Human Resources Staff is also available to explain to you about various employment benefits offered and answer any other HR related questions you may have  Please contact VMI s Human Resource Office for any questions regarding in processing  Relocating to Lexington   VMI is a public  four year  undergraduate military college  1 200 students  located in the historic Shenandoah Valley of Virginia  Lexington  population 7 000  also home to Washington   Lee University  offers a stimulating cultural atmosphere  a relaxed rural pace  and a diverse economic base to make life both pleasant and rewarding  The following websites provide information on Lexington and the surrounding area  Lexington Virginia s Visitor Information Lexington Rockbridge Chamber of Commerce Moving   Relocation Expenses Whether you want to rent or own  there are a variety of real estate companies available to help make your transition to Lexington as smooth as possible  When selecting a new residence  be aware that many public utilities  such as sewer and water  are unavailable outside the city limits  Check with your realtor for further information  A directory of the real estate companies registered with the Chamber of Commerce is listed on website above  Please contact your VMI department for questions regarding relocation  We look forward to working with you  VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu Virginia Military Institute   New Employee Information  skip to content VMI VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI Menu About About Us Administrative Offices Institute Report News  Photos  Videos VMI Archives Museums VMI Museum System The VMI Museum New Market Battlefield Stonewall Jackson House For Visitors Directions   Map Employment Parents   Family Conferences Chessie Nature Trail Bookstore Resources MyVMI Directories Friendly URLs Post View Health and Safety Computing Academics Areas of Study Majors   Minors Arts   Humanities Engineering Information   Social Sciences Life Sciences Natural Sciences ROTC Enrichment Institute Honors Program International Programs Service Opportunities Summer Programs Institute Writing Program Research Support Cadet Counseling Career Services Disabilities Services Miller Academic Center Advising Math Resource Center The Writing Center Resources Registrar Financial Aid Canvas Login Dean s Office Career Services Bookstore Cadet Computing Admissions Corps Life Athletics Library   Archives Preston Library Library Home Find Books Departments Media Equipment Technical Services Visitor Information Archives Archives Home Online Exhibits VMI History FAQs Genealogy   Alumni Manuscripts Civil War   New Market Give Close Menu Human Resources Employment Opportunities Benefits   Services For Employees Current Employees New Employees Training Policies HR Forms Staff Inclement Weather Policy Fraud  Waste   Abuse Hotline P   540  464 7322 F   540  464 7299  E  hroffice vmi edu Human Resources Office Virginia Military Institute 305 Letcher Avenue Lexington  VA 24450 Home   Administrative Offices   Finance   Administration   HR   New Employee Information New Employee Information Welcome to Virginia Military Institute  We are excited that you have chosen us as your employer and will be joining the VMI community  We hope you find your new career at VMI both challenging and rewarding  In Processing On your first day of employment  you will visit Human Resources to fill out various employment  tax  and payroll forms  Please refer to the Employment Forms listed under the HR Forms link on the left side of the webpage for a complete list of the forms  Ensure that you bring the required identification document s  necessary to complete the I 9 Employment Verification Eligibility form  The Human Resources Staff is also available to explain to you about various employment benefits offered and answer any other HR related questions you may have  Please contact VMI s Human Resource Office for any questions regarding in processing  Relocating to Lexington   VMI is a public  four year  undergraduate military college  1 200 students  located in the historic Shenandoah Valley of Virginia  Lexington  population 7 000  also home to Washington   Lee University  offers a stimulating cultural atmosphere  a relaxed rural pace  and a diverse economic base to make life both pleasant and rewarding  The following websites provide information on Lexington and the surrounding area  Lexington Virginia s Visitor Information Lexington Rockbridge Chamber of Commerce Moving   Relocation Expenses Whether you want to rent or own  there are a variety of real estate companies available to help make your transition to Lexington as smooth as possible  When selecting a new residence  be aware that many public utilities  such as sewer and water  are unavailable outside the city limits  Check with your realtor for further information  A directory of the real estate companies registered with the Chamber of Commerce is listed on website above  Please contact your VMI department for questions regarding relocation  We look forward to working with you  VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu Virginia Military Institute   New Employee Information       Virginia Military Institute   New Employee Information                     skip to content VMI VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI Menu About About Us Administrative Offices Institute Report News  Photos  Videos VMI Archives Museums VMI Museum System The VMI Museum New Market Battlefield Stonewall Jackson House For Visitors Directions   Map Employment Parents   Family Conferences Chessie Nature Trail Bookstore Resources MyVMI Directories Friendly URLs Post View Health and Safety Computing Academics Areas of Study Majors   Minors Arts   Humanities Engineering Information   Social Sciences Life Sciences Natural Sciences ROTC Enrichment Institute Honors Program International Programs Service Opportunities Summer Programs Institute Writing Program Research Support Cadet Counseling Career Services Disabilities Services Miller Academic Center Advising Math Resource Center The Writing Center Resources Registrar Financial Aid Canvas Login Dean s Office Career Services Bookstore Cadet Computing Admissions Corps Life Athletics Library   Archives Preston Library Library Home Find Books Departments Media Equipment Technical Services Visitor Information Archives Archives Home Online Exhibits VMI History FAQs Genealogy   Alumni Manuscripts Civil War   New Market Give Close Menu Human