l forms  Please refer to the Employment Forms listed under the HR Forms link on the left side of the webpage for a complete list of the forms  Ensure that you bring the required identification document s  necessary to complete the I 9 Employment Verification Eligibility form  The Human Resources Staff is also available to explain to you about various employment benefits offered and answer any other HR related questions you may have  Please contact VMI s Human Resource Office for any questions regarding in processing  Relocating to Lexington   VMI is a public  four year  undergraduate military college  1 200 students  located in the historic Shenandoah Valley of Virginia  Lexington  population 7 000  also home to Washington   Lee University  offers a stimulating cultural atmosphere  a relaxed rural pace  and a diverse economic base to make life both pleasant and rewarding  The following websites provide information on Lexington and the surrounding area  Lexington Virginia s Visitor Information Lexington Rockbridge Chamber of Commerce Moving   Relocation Expenses Whether you want to rent or own  there are a variety of real estate companies available to help make your transition to Lexington as smooth as possible  When selecting a new residence  be aware that many public utilities  such as sewer and water  are unavailable outside the city limits  Check with your realtor for further information  A directory of the real estate companies registered with the Chamber of Commerce is listed on website above  Please contact your VMI department for questions regarding relocation  We look forward to working with you Human Resources Employment Opportunities Benefits   Services For Employees Current Employees New Employees Training Policies HR Forms Staff Inclement Weather Policy Fraud  Waste   Abuse Hotline P   540  464 7322 F   540  464 7299  E  hroffice vmi edu Human Resources Office Virginia Military Institute 305 Letcher Avenue Lexington  VA 24450  Human Resources Employment 